tent\",\"title\":\"Fetch Website HTML\"}}`, you must perform the following steps:\n1. **Bottleneck Analysis**: Audit the input HTML to identify specific instances of unoptimized SVGs, S3-hosted videos lacking a CDN, excessive React hydration on static elements, verbose HTML for tickers, and SEO failures (missing JSON-LD, multiple H1 tags, absence of robots.txt/sitemap.xml).\n2. **Architectural Design**: Define an \"Architecture de Islas\" (Islands Architecture) strategy. Detail which components remain static in Astro and which require selective hydration for interactivity.\n3. **Compute Layer Specification**: Design a \"Capa de Cómputo\" using Rust/WASM to handle high-performance requirements, specifically \"NanoBot\" lead parsing and complex KPI calculations.\n4. **Infrastructure Planning**: Detail the \"Infraestructura Modernizada\" utilizing Cloudflare Pages or Netlify for deployment, Neon Postgres for the database, and R2 for asset storage.\n5. **Monorepo Structure**: Propose a monorepo organization that encompasses both the marketing site and the dashboard application.\n6. **Implementation Roadmap**: Create a 3-sprint execution plan (Sprint 1: Core & SEO; Sprint 2: Assets & Edge; Sprint 3: Dash & WASM) with specific deliverables and technical targets.\n\n## Definitions and Specifications\n- **Target Stack**: Astro (Meta-framework) + Rust/WASM (Compute).\n- **Islands Architecture**: Astro for zero-JS by default, with selective hydration for specific interactive components.\n- **Compute Tasks**: \n    - NanoBot lead parsing: High-speed extraction of lead data.\n    - KPI Calculations: Real-time data processing for the dashboard.\n- **Infrastructure Components**:\n    - **Deployment**: Cloudflare Pages or Netlify.\n    - **Database**: Neon Postgres (Serverless).\n    - **Storage**: Cloudflare R2 (S3-compatible object storage).\n- **Performance Targets (Success Criteria)**:\n    - **LCP (Largest Contentful Paint)**: < 1.5 seconds.\n    - **Image Optimization**: 80%