y preambles. Just the output, please."}]},"config$ask-user":false,"strategy":"All at once"}},{"id":"node_step_migration_plan","metadata":{"title":"Render Migration Plan Webpage","visual":{"x":1620,"y":340,"collapsed":"expanded","outputHeight":88},"step_intent":"Render the 'detailed_migration_strategy_text' into a well-formatted and professional HTML webpage. The webpage should clearly present the technical diagnosis, the proposed Astro + Rust/WASM architecture, the implementation roadmap, and any other relevant details from the generated strategy in an easily digestible and presentable format suitable for technical documentation."},"type":"embed://a2/a2.bgl.json#module:render-outputs","configuration":{"text":{"parts":[{"text":"The webpage should present the technical migration strategy in a professional, modern, and highly readable format, fully adhering to the aesthetic and design language established by the provided Asio marketing site HTML and CSS. The goal is a premium, technical documentation feel that is consistent with the Asio brand.\n\n**Layout Organization:**\n\n1.  **Overall Structure:**\n    *   The page will begin with the existing `nav` bar and `marquee-wrap` elements for brand continuity.\n    *   A prominent `hero`-like section will serve as the page title, setting the context for the migration strategy.\n    *   The core content will be structured into distinct, logical sections, each using the `.section` class for consistent vertical spacing and centered within a `.container`.\n    *   The page will conclude with the existing `footer` element.\n\n2.  **Header & Title:**\n    *   Replace the main `hero` section's content with a `tag` like \"Technical Strategy\" and a main `h1` title: \"A Comprehensive Migration Strategy to Astro + Rust/WASM.\" A concise `p` tag can follow, summarizing the document's intent.\n\n3.  **Main Content Sections:**\n    *   **Technical Diagnosis: The Current State**\n        *   This section will start with an `h2` using `.